comments.message:
Could you please annotate returns types and parameters of (at least) public methods as @Nullable and @NotNull?
Believe me, it will save you from a lot of NPEs. It will also save time of these methods callers who will always know the nullity part of the contract.
Kotlin has even introduced special behavior and special language constructs for the NPE problem. But these annotations in Java are quite handy as well. Why don't you use them?

No we shouldn't
Here we have one interface for all operations according to Subversion design

So it would be called for all operations, also for those that do not need such handlers

Maybe further I will create adapters, and this class would be used directly for standartization only - to provide standard interface
